00:14:32.000 --> 00:14:42.000
Or a really cool option is instead to write this model prediction function to Snowflake as a view.

00:14:42.000 --> 00:14:46.000
If you're not familiar with what a view is, a view is basically a SQL query.

00:14:46.000 --> 00:14:49.000
It's a table that exists as a SQL query.

00:14:49.000 --> 00:14:55.000
It's a SQL query that you can save into any database, Snowflake in particular,

00:14:55.000 --> 00:14:57.000
but pretty much any database supports views.

00:14:57.000 --> 00:15:04.000
And what you can do there is anytime that view is called, that query runs.

00:15:06.000 --> 00:15:13.000
So what I'm going to do is create some SQL to create a Snowflake view.

00:15:14.000 --> 00:15:18.000
So what I do is, what I'm going to do is take my full lending club table.

00:15:19.000 --> 00:15:22.000
