00:15:22.000 --> 00:15:26.000
This is a really cool feature of orbital.

00:15:26.000 --> 00:15:32.000
What it's doing here, what orbital inline does is instead of converting the model object to SQL,

00:15:32.000 --> 00:15:34.000
it converts it to dplyr statements.

00:15:35.000 --> 00:15:43.000
And because I'm using dbplyr here, what this does is it means that those dplyr statements can then be converted themselves into SQL.

00:15:44.000 --> 00:15:46.000
So you see me create a...

00:15:47.000 --> 00:15:51.000
